  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ICRC/Support in Syria, 2013</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ICRC works with Syrian Arab Red Crescent (SARC) to assist people affected by armed conflict and other situations of violence and to improve water supply/sanitation. Furthermore, ICRC seek to visit people detained, acts as a neutral intermediary in issues of humanitarian concern for Syrian inhabitants of the Golan occupied by Israel, facilitates travel for certain categories of persons between the occupied Golan and the Syrian Arab Republic, and helps separated relatives maintain contact. As the conflict in Syria continued unabated, the ICRC scaled up its humanitarian operations to keep up with the needs of conflict-affected people. A revised appeal was issued in May 2013, increasing the support in areas such as food, non-food items, water and sanitation and health services.</narrative>
  </description>
